00:24:26.056 --> 00:24:30.036
41X. And for our somatic, we're targeting 100X, and we're getting a median

433
00:24:30.076 --> 00:24:33.746
of around 121. And you can see the tumor purity and

434
00:24:33.776 --> 00:24:35.876
homozygosity is pretty good. We are

435
00:24:37.096 --> 00:24:38.676
assessing

436
00:24:40.256 --> 00:24:44.076
tumor cellularity before we move on with sequencing, and so we're trying to

437
00:24:44.116 --> 00:24:46.676
skew towards high enough tumor cellularity.

438
00:24:47.976 --> 00:24:50.816
This is my most favorite slide in this deck.

439
00:24:51.336 --> 00:24:54.345
We decided to overlay our data with 1000 Genome and

440
00:24:54.996 --> 00:24:55.516
human

441
00:24:56.816 --> 00:25:00.296
HDGP data, really to kind of see is TACA data

442
00:25:00.336 --> 00:25:04.256
distinguishable from the "gold standard" data that's

443
00:25:04.296 --> 00:25:07.836
currently available. And as you can see here, it is

444
00:25:07.916 --> 00:25:08.756
indistinguishable.

445
00:25:10.036 --> 00:25:13.496
So the triangles are TACA data. We've overlaid it

446
00:25:13.536 --> 00:25:17.416
with data from these well-established databases.

447
00:25:17.446 --> 00:25:21.416
And as you can see, our data perfectly aligns with the African

448
00:25:21.496 --> 00:25:23.635
ancestry data that's already in these databases.

449
00:25:24.016 --> 00:25:27.756
You can see the Ghana and Nigeria samples cluster slightly closer

450
00:25:27.796 --> 00:25:30.316
together with the Kenyan samples slightly down.

451
00:25:30.336 --> 00:25:34.036
And then you can see the Seychelles data demonstrating admixture with South

452
00:25:34.076 --> 00:25:38.016
Asian, which makes a lot of sense. So basically, this is the sort

453
00:25:38.116 --> 00:25:38.316
of

454
00:25:39.916 --> 00:25:43.796
sanity check slide to show that sequencing done by Yamachi in

455
00:25:43.836 --> 00:25:47.496
TACA is on par with the data that already exists.

456
00:25:48.156 --> 00:25:49.016
And so at least

457
00:25:49.856 --> 00:25:53.556
at this level, I think we can be quite confident on how we move

458
00:25:53.596 --> 00:25:53.896
forward.

459
00:25:55.636 --> 00:25:57.316
We've assessed tumor mutational burden.

460
00:25:57.356 --> 00:26:01.166
There's a lot of conflicting literature about whether African individuals have

