00:39:04.496 --> 00:39:08.076
AUCs were really high, and it showed really nice correlation with...

682
00:39:08.556 --> 00:39:08.946
Excuse me.

683
00:39:24.456 --> 00:39:28.356
Yeah, so there was AUC of 0.94 for LGR1

684
00:39:28.436 --> 00:39:29.456
when we were comparing

685
00:39:30.856 --> 00:39:32.096
pancreatic cancers versus

686
00:39:32.896 --> 00:39:34.516
benign pathologies.

687
00:39:36.396 --> 00:39:39.736
These are all really nice datasets, but they are kind of small, right?

688
00:39:39.816 --> 00:39:39.996
So

689
00:39:42.036 --> 00:39:45.936
the plan is now to really

690
00:39:45.976 --> 00:39:47.136
go into much bigger datasets.

691
00:39:48.196 --> 00:39:52.156
So another study that came out from our lab was a prostate cancer study.

692
00:39:53.116 --> 00:39:53.376
Here,

693
00:39:54.276 --> 00:39:57.846
unfortunately, African men carry a really high incidence and aggressive

694
00:39:57.916 --> 00:39:58.466
phenotypes.

695
00:39:59.456 --> 00:40:02.336
We predict there to be around 4,000 new cases per annum.

696
00:40:03.076 --> 00:40:06.616
And in Southern Africa, for some reason, there's the greatest

697
00:40:06.696 --> 00:40:10.456
incidence across the entire African continent, where 65.1

698
00:40:11.716 --> 00:40:14.976
men per 100,000 will be diagnosed with prostate cancer.

699
00:40:17.376 --> 00:40:21.236
So what did we see in this study? This was done very recently in the last

700
00:40:21.316 --> 00:40:21.796
two years.

